    "NNESOTA HISTORICAL SOCIETY FAUL MINN A FAMILY NEWSPAPER DARE TO DO OUR DUTY Let us have faith that right makes might and in that faith let us to the end dare to do our duty as we understand it Abraham Lincoln VOLUME XXII VOTE SHIFT INTERESTING November sth Elections in East Draw Much Com ment in Country FarmerLaborites Watch AntiSales Tax Platform Win in Kentucky By HENRY G TEIGAN The elections that occurred in sev eral eastern states last week have aroused considerable newspaper com ment Republican newspapers ob viously have attempted to show that the returns indicate a comeback for the G O P Democrats on the other hand are doing their best to have the returns show Franklin D Roosevelt and the New Deal as strong as ever Now it probably matters little to radicalminded folks whether senti ment has shifted from the Democrats to the Republicans or in the opposite direction Fundamentally there is no substantial difference in the pro grams of the two old political parties though it is undoubtedly true that Roosevelt has shown on the whole more progressive tendencies than his Republican predecessors Returns Interesting Yet it is a bit interesting to ex amine"
